[normal]&#xa0;[bold]Written evidence submitted by [bold]World Vision UK[bold]&#xa0;[bold]&#xa0;[bold]World Vision is the world's largest international children's charity. We are 
[normal]a child focused Christian relief, development and advocacy organisation dedicated to working with children, their families and communities to overcome poverty and injustice. We work in 100 countries to improve the lives of 100 million people worldwide.  
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]We welcome the opportunity to provide evidence to the Committee on World Vision’s approach to development work in the Middle East. This submission will 
[normal]primarily
[normal] address DfID’s 
[normal]regional 
[normal]human
[normal]itarian response to the Syria crisis 
[normal]with a primary focus on 
[normal]the
[normal] 
[normal]work with 
[normal]Syrian refugees and the communities hosting them
[normal]. 
